    {
      "id": "82c8dc72402b3110950e0326c7907e40f206c195",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2020-07-17 09:13:01.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\nThe patch seems reasonable, because this is something a user might coincidentally do, but I don't think this should be considered a *fix* for the LU-13794 problem of writing to an FLR file with a failed OST.\n\nDid this work in the past, and some patch broke it, or has this never been tested?  Definitely the MDS should automatically pick a mirror that is not missing objects to avoid this problem.\n\nIn some cases, there may be a race condition where an OST goes offline right after the MDS selected it for a mirror, but I don't think applies here.  If a user noticed the problem and can run \"lfs setstripe\" then the MDS has had lots of time to detect the problem.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
